troduce a blacklist of git annex versions, so we crash informatively when we detect a certain version to be in the range of versions we know we don't support or which exhibit Grave issues?\r\n\r\nIt might eventually get platform specific exclusions.\r\n\r\nAnd probably by default we should provide ceiling version to the next major version of git annex. If new one gets out and is compatible with us, should be easy to kick out maint release.\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/4272/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/4272/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}